EPOCHS = 50
BATCHSIZE = 100
LEARNING_RATE = 1e-3
In [4]:
(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = tf.keras.datasets.mnist.load_data()
x_train = (x_train / 255.).astype(np.float32)[..., None]
x_test = (x_test / 255.).astype(np.float32)[..., None]
y_train = y_train.astype(np.int)
y_test = y_test.astype(np.int)
In [5]:
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(
        filters=20, kernel_size=5, strides=(1, 1), padding='VALID',
    ),
    tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(),
    tf.keras.layers.ReLU(),
    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(
        filters=20, kernel_size=5, strides=(1, 1), padding='VALID',
    ),
    tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D(),
    tf.keras.layers.ReLU(),
    tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(units=100),
    tf.keras.layers.ReLU(),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(units=10),
])
In [6]:
optimizer = tf.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=LEARNING_RATE)

for e in range(1, EPOCHS + 1):
    loss_list = []
    accuracy_list = []
    for i in range(0, len(x_train), BATCHSIZE):
        x = x_train[i: i + BATCHSIZE]
        y = y_train[i: i + BATCHSIZE]
        with tf.GradientTape() as tape:
            logits = model(x)
            loss = tf.reduce_mean(
                tf.nn.sparse_softmax_cross_entropy_with_logits(
                    y, logits
                )
            )
        loss_list.append(loss.numpy())
        accuracy_list.append(
            np.mean(y == np.argmax(logits.numpy(), axis=-1))
        )
        grads = tape.gradient(loss, model.trainable_variables)
        optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(grads, model.trainable_variables))
    print(
        f"Epoch={e:2}, "
        f"Accuracy={np.mean(accuracy_list) * 100:5.02f}%, "
        f"Loss={np.mean(loss_list):6.04f}")
    indices = np.random.permutation(len(x_train))
    x_train = x_train[indices]
    y_train = y_train[indices]

In [7]:
probabilities = tf.nn.softmax(model(x_test)).numpy()
predictions = np.argmax(probabilities, axis=-1)
print("Ground Truth (row) x Prediction (col)")
print(confusion_matrix(y_test, predictions))
print(f"Accuracy = {np.mean(y_test == predictions) * 100}%")
